citeinfo.title: Diets and Food Web Relationships of Seabirds in the Gulf of Alaska and Adjacent Marine Regions 1986 - OCSEAP

abstract.p: Overall diets of 39 species of marine birds (four procellariiforms, three cormorants, six sea ducks, one phalarope, two jaegers, 17 gulls, two terns and 13 alcids) inhabiting the Gulf of Alaska and adjacent marine regions are summarized with food web diagrams, tables and text.

[Reference: Sanger, G. A. 1986. Diets and food web relationships of seabirds in the Gulf of Alaska and adjacent marine regions, Final Reports of Principal Investigators, OCSEAP Final Rep., 45(1986), p. 631-771, NOAA, U.S. Dep. Commer.] ARLIS Reference Call Number FWLB1039 .
